[Defining the causal agent, an H5 avian influenza strain, as being an LPAI
(low pathogenic avian influenza) is premature at the present stage of the
investigation. The full typing (including the N type) and the pathogenicity
of the virus should be determined according to a prescribed protocol;
reportedly, these tests are expected to be performed, in this case, at the
reference laboratory in Australia, namely CSIRO, Australian Animal Health
Laboratory (AAHL), Geelong, Victoria, Australia. The other 6 reference
OIE/FAO labs for avian influenza are situated in Japan, Italy, the USA,
Germany (2 labs), and the UK. - Mod.AS]
[Elsevier reference:
Editorial. Avian influenza: perfect storm now gathering? Lancet.
2005. 365:820 <http://tinyurl.com/bglqq>]
